cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper discusses a state-of-the-art Knowledge Graph Management System, Vadalog, which combines logical reasoning with machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent agents and systems that can reason, learn, and perceive their environment. 

The paper also discusses data wrangling tasks, which fall under the sub-category cs.DB (Databases), as well as probabilistic reasoning, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also emphasizes the importance of seamless integration with modern data science toolkits, such as the Jupyter platform, which falls under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). 

Finally, Vadalog is a programming language for knowledge representation and reasoning, which falls under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages).
